note:
3月2日（路透社）-商业软件巨头甲骨文公司（ORCL.N）周三表示，已暂停在俄罗斯的所有业务，而竞争对手SAP SE（SAPG.DE）随后宣布，将暂停在俄罗斯的所有销售活动，此前该公司在莫斯科&#39；美国入侵乌克兰。
甲骨文&#39；在乌克兰#39；美国数字转型部长在推特上向两家公司寻求支持。阅读更多
甲骨文没有回应就其推文发表详细评论的请求，该推文称该公司&#34；已经暂停了在俄罗斯联邦的所有行动&#34;
SAP在周二的一篇博客文章中称对俄罗斯实施经济制裁&#34；这是恢复和平努力中的一个重要机制&#34;
&#34;根据制裁，我们正在停止在俄罗斯的业务，此外，暂停SAP服务和产品在俄罗斯的所有销售，&#34；首席执行官克里斯蒂安·克莱因写道。
他说，除了最初向乌克兰提供100万欧元（111万美元）的人道主义援助外，SAP还有&#34；还提议将我们在欧洲各地的办公场所改造成仓库和难民住宿场所&#34;
达拉斯的Sheila Dang和加利福尼亚奥克兰的Paresh Dave报道。马修·刘易斯编辑

note_en:
March 2 (Reuters) - Business software giant Oracle Corp  (ORCL.N) said on Wednesday it has suspended all operations in Russia, while rival SAP SE  (SAPG.DE) later announced it would pause all sales in the country following Moscow&#39;s invasion of Ukraine.
 Oracle&#39;s announcement on Twitter came about three hours after Ukraine&#39;s minister of digital transformation tweeted at the two companies asking for support.   read more
 Oracle did not respond to requests for comment to elaborate on its tweet, which said the company &#34;has already suspended all operations in the Russian Federation.&#34;
  SAP in a blog post on Tuesday called economic sanctions against Russia &#34;an important mechanism in the efforts to restore peace.&#34;
 &#34;We are stopping business in Russia aligned with sanctions and, in addition, pausing all sales of SAP services and products in Russia,&#34; Chief Executive Christian Klein wrote.
 He said that in addition to an initial 1 million euros ($1.11 million) in humanitarian support toward Ukraine, SAP had &#34;also offered to convert our office space at locations across Europe into warehousing and accommodation for refugees.&#34;
   Reporting by Sheila Dang in Dallas and Paresh Dave in Oakland, Calif.Editing by Matthew Lewis
